# {{ project_name | title }}

## Development
Development is conducted inside development containers. VS Code handles most
container management (build, start, stop) automatically when you open the
project ; outside of VS Code, you can use `just` recipes (see
[devcontainers.just](./.recipes/devcontainers.just)

Build time secrets are stored in `.devcontainer/env.local` ; run time secrets
are stored in the `.env.local` file. Both files are not committed to the
repository, instead `.devcontainer/env` and `.env` files act as templates.

To set up your development environment from the CLI, use `just
devcontainer::up`.

### Project lifecycle
This project uses [`just`](https://just.systems/) as a command runner. Run `just`
(or `just --list`) to see all available recipes. Key commands:

| Command                       | Description                                                                       |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `just setup`                  | Install dependencies, configure pre-commit hooks, and set up the dev environment  |
| `just devcontainers::up`      | Build and start the dev container, then open a shell inside it                    |
| `just devcontainers::stop`    | Stop the running dev container                                                    |
| `just devcontainers::down`    | Remove the dev container                                                          |
| `just template::update`       | Update the project from the latest copier template                                |
| `just template::check-update` | Check whether a template update is available                                      |
| `just release::check`         | Print unreleased commits and the proposed next version                            |
| `just release::release`       | Interactively draft a release: bump version, update changelog, commit and tag     |
| `just release::push`          | Push commits and tags to the remote                                               |

### Installing dependencies
Install libraries from pypi using: `pdm add <LIB>`. The library will appear in
[`pyproject.toml`](./pyproject.toml). You may specify a `--group` or a optional
dependencies or dependency groups, see [pdm
documentation](https://pdm-project.org/en/latest/usage/dependency/) for more
information.

### Versioning and changelog
This project follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/) and uses
[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) (`feat:`, `fix:`,
`chore:`, etc.). Human readable release notes are maintained in
[`CHANGELOG.md`](./CHANGELOG.md).

New releases are drafted using `git-cliff` via `just release::` recipes.

### Project architecture
The project is organized as follows:

```
.recipes/               # Recipes modules for just, see also `justfile`
.devcontainer/          # Dev container configuration and setup
├── devcontainer.json   # Root configuration
├── Containerfile       # Container definition
├── setup.sh            # Optional, per user, git-untracked configuration
src/
├── {{ package_name}}/  # {{ project_name | title }} package
│   ├── __init__.py     # Package initialization
README.md               # Documentation root
CHANGELOG.md            # Human readable list of changes
justfile                # List of recipes
.env                    # Template configuration
.env.local              # Per-user, git-untracked secrets and environment
```
